column3: BEGIN of Power on EGSE Sequence
Switch on CLD via Battery & check voltage (24 Volt)
Switch on the primary and secondary supply switches on the Control Panel
Switch on Sup_24V_20A & check voltage (ca. 27,2 Volt)
Switch on Sup_24V_10A & check voltage (ca. 27,2 Volt)
Switch on Sup_12V_10A & check voltage (ca. 13,8 Volt)
Switch on Bat_24V_20A & check voltage (ca. 27,9 Volt)
Switch on Bat_24V_10A & check voltage (ca. 27,9 Volt)
Switch on Bat_12V_10A & check voltage (ca. 13,8 Volt)
Remove 7 Grounding Bridges and leave EPS_BAT inserted
Insert EPS_EXT Fuse in Power Supply Control Panel
Confirm green LED at EPS_EXT Fuse is on
Insert Main_Bus Fuse in Power Supply Control Panel
Confirm LED at Main_Bus Fuse is OFF. Else Pull fuse and insert all Grounding Bridges
Set remaining Fuses (except Payload Fuse) and check for green LED
Confirm Main bus LED is on.
Confirm Main Chute button is disabled
Confirm green LED at Payload Fuse is on
Remove Pneumatic Line from Fueling arm
Reattach Pneumatic Line to Fueling arm
Confirm that Ignition Umbilical is disconnected
BEGIN EGSE Valve and actuator check Sequence
Check if video recording is enabled @ MCC
Switch OxDV to closed & check if magnetic valve LED is on
Switch HPDV to closed & check if magnetic valve LED is on
Verify Bottle Temperatures @ OxT1, OxT2, HPT2
Verify Water Temperatures @ Ox@T1, OxWT2, HPWT2
Check if all valve switches are in OFF position (Except OxDV & HPDV)
Check loadcell by applying force to it
Switch on N2O coupling & check if magnetic valve LED is on
Switch on HE coupling & check if magnetic valve LED is on
Switch on swivle arm & check if magnetic valve LED is on
Switch off swivel arm & HE coupling & N2O coupling
Confirm that Ignition Umbilical is disconnected
Plug in Bridges B1 and B2
Turn on Ignition Switch for 2 Second & Confirm ignition signal received at sbRio
Confirm that all hatches are closed
Check HE bottle 1 connector is attached
Check HE bottle 2 connector is attached
Check N2O bottle 1 connector is attached
Check N2O bottle 2 connector is attached
Check hose between HPSM & N2OSM is connected on both ends
Check hose between HPSM & Flight Segment is connected on both ends
Check hose between N2OSM & Flight Segment is connected on both ends
Check Pneumatik hose is connected on both ends
Move into Position to open HE Bottle 1
Check & compare pressure HPPT1 with HPPG1 (max 300 bar)
Check Gastech Silver HPPR1 (max 300 to 50 bar)
Open & Close HPV1 SHORTLY & Check HPPT1
Open & Close HPV2 SHORTLY & Check HPPT2 0 bar
Open & Close HPDV SHORTLY & Check HPLPT 0 bar
Close HE Bottle 1 and check HPSM for leakage (If leakage occurs Abort)
Check and compare pressure HPPT1 with HPPG1 0 Bar
Turn on GoPro Camera at end of Launch Rail
Powercycle EPS to to start flight mode on Telemega
BEGIN Pressure Test Flight Segment (PHASE YELLOW)
Open & Close stepwise MPV1/MPV2 to 50 Bar @ OxInPT1 & OxInPT2
Check & compare OxInPT1 with OxInPG1 based on Bottle temperature (max 50 bar)
Check & compare pressure OxInPT2 with OxInPG2 based on Bottle temperature (max 50 bar)
Check Temperature of N2O Bottle 1 @OxT1 & OxWT1 (max 22C)
Check Temperature of N2O Bottle 2 @OxT2 & OxWT2 (max 22C)
Check & compare pressure HPPT2 with HPPG2 (max 315 bar)
Check & compare pressure OxInPT 1 with OxInPG 1 (max 50 bar)
Check & compare pressure OxInPT 2 with OxInPG 2 (max 50 bar)
Insert Ignition Bridges B1 and B2 into EGSE
Begin of Ox FUELING Sequence (PHASE RED)
Confirm that STX3 Package received by email
Open & Close HPV1 to 50 Bar @ ROxTPT (stop at 30 bar and wait 30 seconds to check for leakage)
Open & Close HPV1 to more than 50 Bar @ RHPPT and check ROxTPT 50 Bar
Open RDV shortly, to check tightness @ RHPPT & ROxTPT (If leakages occur Abort)
Open & Close stepwise MPV3 to 50 Bar @ OxOutPT
Check if RHPPT & ROxTPT more than OxInPT1, If less Open & Close HPV1
Open stepwise RDV until N2O bottle empty or 25kg OxTankMass, keep temperatures RDVT and RDVET above 10°C and Check delta ROxTPT and OxInPT1
Check if Pressure rises in OxPT1, if Pressure rises relief via OxV1 or wait for Pressure relief valve
Check & compare RHPPT & ROxTPT 50 Bar and more than OxInPT2, If less Open & Close HPV1
Open stepwise RDV to 25kg OxTankMass, keep temperatures RDVT and RDVET above 10°C and Check delta OxTPT and OxInPT1
Check if Pressure rises in OxPT2, if Pressure rises relief via OxV2 or wait for Pressure relief valve
Open stepwise OxDV until OxOutPT 0 Bar
Provied OxTankMass and Temperature Readings to Windwaiting Station
Confirm End of Oxidator Fueling to OPS
Start Video Recording in Block House
BEGIN Switching to Internal Power Sequence
Confirm EPS Voltages are within limits
Check if videorecording @ MCC is running
Open and close HPV1 stepwise until RHPPT 300 Bar or pressure equal to HE Bottle 1
Open and close HPV2 stepwise until RHPPT 300 Bar
Open and close HPDV stepwise until HPLPT 0 Bar
Check for leakage HPLPT 0 Bar & RHPPT 300 Bar
Confirm End of Fueling to OPS
BEGIN  of Moving Fueling Arm Away Sequence
Move fueling arm away from rocket
Confirm Fueling Arm away to OPS
T+20: Verify RMOxOV Closed and RMOxSV Open (Cruise)
T+310: Verify Main Chute Deployed and RDV Open (Main)
START OF PASSIVATION (PHASE YELLOW) (Write down Time)
Check ROxTPT & RHPPT 1 Bar, if more: Open & Close stepwise RDV
Go to Testrig, close N2O Bottle 1 & N2O Bottle 2 and return to Block House
Go to MRL, confirm OxInPG1 & OxInPG2 0 Bar, else return to Block House, then close HE Bottle
Write down remaining Pressure of HE Bottle
Go to Testrig, confirm HPPG2 0 Bar, else return to Block House, then open ComTerm
Write down remaining Pressure of HE Bottle
Check EPV manometer less than 6 bar
Check and compare pressure HPPT1 with HPPG1
Turn off area warning light and open barrier
END OF PASSIVATION (PHASE GREEN) (Write down Time)
Turn off GoPro & Camcorder & Stop Block House Video recording
Copy PID.vi.tdms & save to new name
Wait for buffer storage process to be finished
save data files from cRIO to PC
Save video & audio data on external HDD
Stop RT_CD.vi and save logfile to external HDD
